18 January - Italian Sponge Cake 

- 4   large eggs, separated
- 1   teaspoon vanilla
- 3/4 cup sugar
- 1/2 cup flour
- 1/2 cup cornstarch 
-     pinch of salt

Butter and line with paper a 9-10" round cake pan, 2" deep. Whisk egg yolks with vanilla, add half of the sugar and whisk till frothy about 5 minutes by hand or mixer. Sift flour and cornstarch together. Beat egg whites with salt, form soft peaks. Beating faster add remaining sugar slowly, forming firm peaks. Fold yolk mixture into whites, sift flour and cornstarch over eggs in 3 additions, folding them in gradually. Pour in pan, bake at 350F for 30-40 minutes till well risen. Loosen the sides, invert onto rack and leave paper stuck on it. Turn right side up and cool on rack. 

Variations
Flavor the batter with 1 teaspoon grated orange or lemon zest or 1 tablespoon anisette. 